As a result of the measures adopted since 2009, the share of new voters registered has decreased by 17% in 2010 compared to 2006.
In addition, Republican legislators in five other states have passed laws aimed at shortening the time for early voting.
For example, in the 2008 Florida general election, 33% of voters who voted in advance were African-Americans, although they made up only 13% of the state's voters.
The same applies to the Hispanic population.
