On that day, some Walmart employees, of whom there are 2.2 million worldwide, dropped their work and pushed together with trade unions and leftist activists to the chain’s branches, whose target group is low- and middle-income people.
Walmart sells all products, from diapers to hunting rifles and car batteries to vacuum cleaners, eggs and milk.
The merchandise in the Walmart stores is on average between 8 and 27% cheaper than in large supermarkets.
That’s why many of the low-paid Walmart employees only buy from their own workplace.
