<0xC5><0xA0>imon Ornest: At our concerts we want to gather positive energy
What do you think about the end of the world in less than a month?
This is one of those reports of disasters that we people so gladly respond to.
With our band The Tap Tap, we are more likely to make fun of it and say that we are the only band in the world that can gather enough positive energy to stop or prevent the end of the world.
In December, you will also realize a unique project with three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you introduce the project to our readers?
This is a nationwide charity event that we have been planning for two years.
For this we want to use the marketing potential of the Mayan calendar, whose end is predicted for December 21 at 11:10 a.m.
The day before, i.e. on December 20th, three concerts will take place simultaneously from 9 p.m. in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
The end of the concerts is supposed to be around the time when the Mayan calendar ends on the Pacific island of Kiribati, which is in a time zone 12 hours ahead of us.
Who did this idea come from?
Originally probably from me, then we designed the idea together with our graphic designer Honza Augusta.
Not only do we want to collect enough positive energy to prevent the end of the world, but we also want to think with the public about the state in which we hand this world over to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the Mayan calendar, we have also developed a unique collection of shoes, T-shirts, bags and key tags against the end of the world, with the purchase of which people can also support us via www.e-tap.cz.
The band The Tap Tap has also recorded, along with other performers, the so-called anthem against the end of the world with the title "The End of the World falls out".
Even today, the anthem is very popular on YouTube. Will it also be heard at the charity concerts?
Of course, and at the very end, provided that everything works and the end of the world does not take place...
The anthem is to be sung by all performers at all three concerts at the same time.
In addition, the anthems are broadcast live on Czech television in a direct broadcast.
The text of the hymn comes from Tomá<0xC5><0xA1> Hanák, who also plays the main character of Jesus in the video clip, Xindl X also sings with...
How did you work with both of them?
We also cooperate with other personalities of the Czech cultural scene, which is related to the fact that we carry out many charitable events and concerts...
We strive to involve these people intensively in our projects.
It has been shown that most people are interested in working with us and enjoy it.
What is the purpose of the proceeds of the concerts against the end of the world?
For the establishment of the barrier-free educational center Studeo, where we have been working for six years with the association Tap in the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute.
The students of the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute are regularly cared for by lecturers who help them with different leisure activities.
Since the students themselves do not have the means to visit the lecturers, we want to help them in this way.
As part of the completion of the Jedli<0xC4><0x8D>ka Institute, a building of its own will be built, which we will then move into with this project.
At each concert, several groups and performers appear.
