“We have no real precedent we can follow,” he added.
The Washington law, called the I-502, comes into force on December 6, and thus also forms the endpoint of a grey zone where the state licensing system does not yet exist, but ownership is legalized.
And unpleasant practical issues need to be clarified during this time - such as how to agree the state's requirement of "adequate access" to licensed marijuana with a ban on cannabis businesses within 300 meters of schools, parks, playgrounds and childcare facilities.
