I'm not going to retire, I'm going to die here because the volcano has been my whole life.
Even if the sulfur burns the throat and the eyes itch, when the wind suddenly turns and the miners jammed into the thick columns that rise from the crater, the men are so hard that no one complains about serious diseases ... of course, except for the usual breathing problems, osteoarthritis, pain in the knees and blisters on the shoulders, which are damaged by the weight of the heads.
With the basket on his back, at 53 years old, Unainik is only more able to carry 50 kg.
